txt.en: Hármelak is in Dâr Laja.\n\nYou have found and removed the traps Hârmelak has said failed to capture pests and are a danger to her people. She will want to hear the good news.
'You have found all the traps, then? My people are safer for your actions; we thank you. I may have further use for your loyalty, and equal reward.'
Traps for rats can be found along the northern walls of Khabârkhad.\n\nIdentify and remove the pest traps.
Search for pest traps along the northern walls of Khabârkhad
Tilmakhím is to the south of Tâkhdar.\n\nHármelak has asked you to discover where some traps for pests have been laid in Tilmakhím.
Not long ago, traps for rats were placed here

'I greet you, [placeholder]. Your travels have taken you to Tilmakhím in the depths of Takhdâr, so I hear. My sources have cautioned me that pests troubling Umbar-môkh are not under control. It is my understanding you are aware of this matter as well.\n\n'I am told the traps are ensnaring my people, not pests. I ask you to take note of where these traps might be laid, and return to me with clear information regarding their locations.'
'I have heard you have been to Tilmakhím. Why have you not yet removed the pest's traps?'
Tilmakhím is to the south of Tâkhdar, but you know the traps are set along the northern walls of Khabârkhad.\n\nJourney there to search for pest traps.
